<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT -  Res-Care raised to buy.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT -  Res-Care raised to buy.</headline>
<text>
<p>-- Hilliard Lyons analyst Stephen O'Neil said Thursday he upgraded his rating on Res-Care Inc to a buy from hold following the recent decline in the stock price.</p>
<p>-- Res-Care shares were changed at 18-1/4.</p>
<p>-- &quot;Fundamentals remain strong and we forecast 20 percent annual earnings growth for (Res-Care),&quot; O'Neil said.</p>
<p>-- He added the stock is a good buying opportunity for long-term growth-oriented investors.</p>
<p>-- His two- to three-year price target is $27 a share.</p>
<p>Reuters Chicago Newsdesk - 312-408-8787</p>
</text>
